In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @water{1 1/4%cups}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Quarter @lemon{1}. Trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; slice crosswise into 1/4-inch-thick half-moons. Halve, peel, and slice @red onion{1} into 1/4-inch-thick wedges. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{3%tablespoon}, 1/4 tsp @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, a squeeze of lemon juice, and a pinch of salt. Add @water{} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches drizzling consistency.

> Use the rest of the garlic powder in the next step.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add zucchini, onion, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until just beginning to soften, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Open package of @lemon-herb diced chicken thighs{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid.

Add chicken, scallion whites, and remaining garlic powder to pan with veggies; cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in a squeeze of lemon juice. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide lemony rice between plates or shallow bowls; top with chicken and veggies. Drizzle everything with garlic crema and garnish with scallion greens. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.